# bluetooth-beacon-consumer agent guide

This file defines repo-specific requirements for human and automated agents.

## 1) Project goals

- Collect BLE advertisement telemetry from Govee sensors in real time.
- Persist readings to CSV in `sensor_logs/`, with low operational overhead.
- Serve a local dashboard + API for near-real-time monitoring and historical review.
- Keep behavior stable for existing users and automation.

## 2) Architecture summary

- Collector binary: `src/main.rs`
  - Passive BLE scan using `btleplug`.
  - Parses manufacturer data for Govee sensors.
  - Writes one CSV per sensor per month.
  - Archives old CSVs to `.csv.gz` when older than 3 months.
- Dashboard/API binary: `src/bin/dashboard.rs`
  - Axum server on `127.0.0.1:3000`.
  - Serves JSON APIs and static UI from `ui/dist`.
- Frontend: `ui/` (React + Vite + Recharts)
  - Polling view, time-range filters, charts, summary cards, table.

## 3) Non-negotiable compatibility contracts

- Keep API routes stable:
  - `GET /api/sensors`
  - `GET /api/sensors/:id/data`
- Keep `GET /api/sensors/:id/data` response keys stable:
  - `columns`, `rows`, `has_archives`, `partial`, `next_offset`, `warnings`
- Keep 404 behavior for unknown sensors on `/api/sensors/:id/data`.
- Keep query-parameter semantics stable:
  - `all`, `since`, `limit`, `offset`
- Keep CSV filename format stable:
  - `YYYY_MM_<sensor_id>.csv`
  - archives: `YYYY_MM_<sensor_id>.csv.gz`
- Keep CSV header columns stable unless a deliberate, documented breaking change is made.

## 4) OATH/OAuth compatibility requirements

The runtime environment may place this service behind an OATH/OAuth-capable gateway.
Even though this app currently does not implement auth itself, changes must remain
compatible with gateway-managed auth flows.

- Do not add hard auth requirements directly in app code without an explicit opt-in mode.
- Do not rename or remove current API paths/status behavior that gateway rules may target.
- Accept requests with `Authorization` headers without rejecting by default.
- Avoid adding redirect-to-login behavior in backend handlers.
- Preserve CORS behavior expected by local/dev tooling unless a migration is planned.
- If auth is introduced later, make it backward-compatible for local non-auth usage.

## 5) Build and run hints

- Rust checks:
  - `cargo fmt`
  - `cargo check`
  - `cargo test`
- Frontend build:
  - `cd ui`
  - `npm ci`
  - `npm run build`
- Run collector:
  - `cargo run`
- Run dashboard/API:
  - `cargo run --bin dashboard`

## 6) Data and performance guardrails

- Maintain append-only logging behavior.
- Keep file write locking (`fs2`) to prevent interleaved writes.
- Keep row/page limits and truncation warnings to prevent unbounded responses.
- Avoid loading entire long-history datasets into memory without pagination controls.

## 7) Change policy

- Prefer additive changes over breaking changes.
- Update `README.md` and `MANUAL_TESTS.md` when behavior changes.
- Add or update tests for any parser, API contract, or paging/filter behavior changes.
